.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8411755988693476e-53, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8578062928782766e-15, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympic\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"interpretation\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene's purpose\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not at all surprising to find out the beheaded woman was not a reference to the modern dispensationalist idea of Christians being beheaded during the Tribulation after the Rapture, but was a nod to Marie Antoinette, otherwise known as \\\"the beheaded queen.\\\"\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.2095310222856807e-12, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2154, \"end\": 2161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso