\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.2095310222856807e-12, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 8808, \"end\": 8818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.2095310222856807e-12, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the more measured tone\", \"from\": 8598, \"to\": 8620}, {\"ngram\": \"Villodas\", \"from\": 8624, \"to\": 8632}, {\"ngram\": \"the more legitimate concerns\", \"from\": 8637, \"to\": 8665}, {\"ngram\": \"Gray\", \"from\": 8669, \"to\": 8673}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 8699, \"to\": 8716}, {\"ngram\": \"mockery\", \"from\": 8748, \"to\": 8755}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 8776, \"to\": 8787}, {\"ngram\": \"the underside\", \"from\": 8826, \"to\": 8839}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 8843, \"to\": 8848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notice the spectrum of responses here.\", \"from\": 8851, \"to\": 8889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the spectrum\", \"from\": 8858, \"to\": 8870}, {\"ngram\": \"responses\", \"from\": 8874, \"to\": 8883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All the men mentioned above are nonaffirming of LGBTQ people and of drag queens in particular.\", \"from\": 8890, \"to\": 8984, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All the men\", \"from\": 8890, \"to\": 8901}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQ people\", \"from\": 8938, \"to\": 8950}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 8958, \"to\": 8969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In that, they are consistent.\", \"from\": 8985, \"to\": 9014, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they also demonstrate a spectrum of responses in the moment that include: It's also interesting to note how the spectrum of outrage runs from white leaders to Black leaders.\", \"from\": 9015, \"to\": 9193, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a spectrum\", \"from\": 9041, \"to\": 9051}, {\"ngram\": \"responses\", \"from\": 9055, \"to\": 9064}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 9068, \"to\": 9078}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectrum\", \"from\": 9127, \"to\": 9139}, {\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 9143, \"to\": 9150}, {\"ngram\": \"white leaders\", \"from\": 9161, \"to\": 9174}, {\"ngram\": \"Black leaders\", \"from\": 9178, \"to\": 9191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though Villodas and Gray remain unaffirming of LGBTQ people and drag queens, their proximity to the underside of power in Christianity seems to accompany a different approach to the Mohlers and Cospers of the world.\", \"from\": 9194, \"to\": 9414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9321, \"end\": 9333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2510180795722683e-16, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Villodas\", \"from\": 9206, \"to\": 9214}, {\"ngram\": \"Gray\", \"from\": 9219, \"to\": 9223}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQ people\", \"from\": 9246, \"to\": 9258}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 9263, \"to\": 9274}, {\"ngram\": \"their proximity\", \"from\": 9276, \"to\": 9291}, {\"ngram\": \"the underside\", \"from\": 9295, \"to\": 9308}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 9312, \"to\": 9317}, {\"ngram\": \"a different approach\", \"from\": 9353, \"to\": 9373}, {\"ngram\": \"the Mohlers\", \"from\": 9377, \"to\": 9388}, {\"ngram\": \"Cospers\", \"from\": 9393, \"to\": 9400}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 9404, \"to\": 9413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Mohler, \\\"Paris aspires to be the new Babylon, with a drag queen at the center behind the altar.\\\"\", \"from\": 9416, \"to\": 9525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9429, \"end\": 9435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mohler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\"}, {\"begin\": 9438, \"end\": 9443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.321988472522023e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new Babylon\", \"from\": 9458, \"to\": 9473}, {\"ngram\": \"a drag queen\", \"from\": 9480, \"to\": 9492}, {\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 9496, \"to\": 9506}, {\"ngram\": \"the altar\", \"from\": 9514, \"to\": 9523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Al Mohler In other words, Mohler believes in a cultural cosmology where drag queens are in the top floor of the Tower of Babel and Christians are on the bottom.\", \"from\": 9527, \"to\": 9688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9527, \"end\": 9536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Mohler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Al Mohler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Mohler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Mohler\"}, {\"begin\": 9554, \"end\": 9560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mohler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\"}, {\"begin\": 9659, \"end\": 9669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.2095310222856807e-12, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 9540, \"to\": 9551}, {\"ngram\": \"a cultural cosmology\", \"from\": 9572, \"to\": 9592}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 9599, \"to\": 9610}, {\"ngram\": \"the top floor\", \"from\": 9618, \"to\": 9631}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tower\", \"from\": 9635, \"to\": 9644}, {\"ngram\": \"Babel\", \"from\": 9648, \"to\": 9653}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 9676, \"to\": 9686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As wrong as I believe Mohler is on this topic, I actually agree with his metaphor.\", \"from\": 9690, \"to\": 9772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9712, \"end\": 9718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mohler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Mohler\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this topic\", \"from\": 9725, \"to\": 9735}, {\"ngram\": \"his metaphor\", \"from\": 9759, \"to\": 9771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a Babylon-like power dynamic at play here.\", \"from\": 9773, \"to\": 9824, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Babylon-like power dynamic\", \"from\": 9782, \"to\": 9810}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 9814, \"to\": 9818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the placement of the people within the tower needs to be reversed.\", \"from\": 9825, \"to\": 9895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the placement\", \"from\": 9829, \"to\": 9842}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 9846, \"to\": 9856}, {\"ngram\": \"the tower\", \"from\": 9864, \"to\": 9873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reality is that drag queens are on the bottom floor, while white men and Christians in particular are at the top.\", \"from\": 9896, \"to\": 10013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9973, \"end\": 9983, \"title\": \"htt